- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for model-checking, which is a common topic in programming languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with Buechi automata, which are a type of automaton used in formal language theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper compares and proposes improvements to algorithms for model-checking. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the practical performance of model-checking algorithms, which is relevant to software engineering.
